        "comment": {
          "commentType": "FUNCTION",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Required for polymorphic O-glycosylation of the serine-rich repeat protein in this bacteria. Catalyzes the first step in glycosylation by transferring N-acetylglucosamine from UDP-GlcNAc to serine residues in the substrate protein. Part of the accessory SecA2/SecY2 system specifically required to export serine-rich repeat cell wall proteins usually encoded upstream in the same operon"
            }
          ]
        }
